<h2>What is FAA Form 8130-3?</h2>
<p>
FAA Form 8130-3 is an Authorized Release Certificate issued under
U.S. Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) regulations.
It certifies that a part or component meets approved airworthiness standards
and is eligible for installation on certified aircraft.
</p>

<h2>What is EASA Form 1?</h2>
<p>
EASA Form 1 is the European equivalent certificate issued under
European Union Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) regulations.
It confirms compliance with European airworthiness requirements.
</p>

<h2>Why Certification Matters</h2>
<ul>
<li>Ensures regulatory airworthiness compliance</li>
<li>Required for installation on certified aircraft</li>
<li>Mandatory for international export transactions</li>
<li>Provides traceability and documentation history</li>
</ul>

<h2>Can One Certificate Replace the Other?</h2>
<p>
Under certain bilateral aviation safety agreements between authorities,
dual-release certificates may be accepted.
However, operators must always verify with their local aviation authority
before installation.
</p>

